Bionomics . This bivoltine species occurs from 500 to 2300 m and is on the wing in April to mid August. Both generations with strongly differing maculation; spring generation described by Brandt in 1939 as capreata . Modarres Awal ( 1994 & 1997 ) lists poplar and willow as host plants in Iran . The female genitalia (
Fig. 16
) are illustrated here for the first time, and are characterized by: rounded vaginal plate with radial, strong wrinkles; deep ostium; heavy scletotized anthrum and ductus; bursa copulatrix membranous, elongated, without signi.
